It's so loud! Where are you?

22
00:01:05,730 --> 00:01:07,316
Outside.

23
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:08,696
<i>Outside where?</i>

24
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,596
You know where you're roaming about right?

25
00:01:10,620 --> 00:01:14,180
Don't space out and go somewhere weird.

26
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,130
Soon Ho.

27
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:22,176
Why is it so hard?

28
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:25,136
You never say things like that.

29
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,180
Han Seo Woo! Where were you?

30
00:01:29,710 --> 00:01:33,166
<i>I didn't see you there.
Anyway, Kang In Wook is not here.</i>

31
00:01:33,190 --> 00:01:35,426
<i>- I'll try and call him.
- He doesn't answer any calls.</i>

32
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:37,076
<i>That guy!</i>

33
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,676
<i>Maybe he has other plans.</i>

34
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,976
No, no. He just left.

35
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,916
He couldn't wait those few minutes.

36
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:45,096
I'm going to catch him for sure.

37
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,836
Can I go home now?

38
00:01:46,860 --> 00:01:48,370
Yes.

39
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:52,650
Something's going on, right?

40
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,826
Is the recording studio empty?

41
00:01:58,850 --> 00:02:00,230
<i>Yes.</i>

42
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:03,486
I'll go for a little bit.

43
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:05,456
Why?

44
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,106
Recently I've had the best sleep there.

45
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:10,466
What are you talking about? Okay.

46
00:02:10,490 --> 00:02:13,066
He doesn't need a house.

47
00:02:13,090 --> 00:02:15,426
I need a house.

48
00:02:15,450 --> 00:02:19,166
I thought you were going?

49
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:21,426
I'll just open up the recording studio.

50
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:23,656
Leave after doing that.

51
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:26,666
Kang In Wook! I'm so mad!

52
00:02:26,690 --> 00:02:30,760
I just ran out without even
being able to wash my face!

53
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,956
<i>Stop it.</i>

54
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:03,250
<i>I'm telling you to end your
long one-sided love right here.</i>

55
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,925
<i>You said you didn't know what ending means,
and</i>

56
00:04:06,949 --> 00:04:09,470
<i>you didn't understand why you had to end,
right?</i>

57
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:15,486
<i>My one-sided love has at least 1% chance.</i>

58
00:04:15,510 --> 00:04:17,910
<i>You're probably wondering,
who says I have 1% chance?</i>

59
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:20,980
<i>It's because he's alive.</i>

60
00:04:23,050 --> 00:04:25,386
<i>You don't even have 1% chance.</i>

61
00:04:25,410 --> 00:04:27,570
<i>So stop.</i>

62
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:33,736
<i>I'm sorry, so I"m going to stop too.</i>

63
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,906
<i>I'm going to stop even my
1% chance of one-sided love.</i>

64
00:04:35,930 --> 00:04:40,250
<i>You, should have stopped earlier.</i>

65
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,870
<i>Did you turn on the music?</i>

66
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:12,550
<i>The music playing now, are good
music for falling asleep to, I heard.</i>

67
00:05:19,490 --> 00:05:22,260
Sleep well.

68
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:01,540
<i>A Piece of Your Mind</i>

69
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:04,780
<i>Episode Six</i>

70
00:06:05,810 --> 00:06:08,846
You came out to see me in?

71
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,356
You ate dinner, right?

72
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:13,636
Yes. You came out knowing I was tired,
right?

73
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:15,496
This feels nice.

74
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,546
You're having a hard time again?

75
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:18,476
Yes.

76
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,770
A roommate is supposed to come in tonight.

77
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:23,576
Since when were we roommates?

78
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:27,286
Everyone except you two are roommates.
I don't want to become attached to you.

79
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:30,736
