really have the attached feeling.

80
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,960
Oh! He's coming.

81
00:06:42,090 --> 00:06:44,830
Student Bae Jin Soo?

82
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:47,946
Hello. I am Bae Jin Soo.

83
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:50,636
Oh. You're wearing a
padded jacket in April.

84
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,980
Do you have anymore stuff?

85
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:58,126
Concert... I think it's you.

86
00:06:58,150 --> 00:07:00,386
I used to be in a orchestra
unit in medical school.

87
00:07:00,410 --> 00:07:02,176
We asked if you have any more things?

88
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,776
More will be delivered
tomorrow by a delivery service.

89
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:08,006
Your gown is so dirty!

90
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:10,426
Take it off as soon as you head in.
I'll wash it for you.

91
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:13,326
The gown that a doctor
wears should be clean.

92
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:15,400
I'm just a student though.

93
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,652
Suna from Senegal said she
became an athlete swimmer.

94
00:07:18,676 --> 00:07:20,786
<i>I will do my best. Take care.
I love you, Teacher. I miss you.</i>

95
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:23,586
I'm so proud of this kid
who has been struggling.

96
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,426
<i>Something happened to you, right?</i>

97
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:28,810
<i>You're calling me and reading a letter.</i>

98
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,510
I got caught.

99
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:36,616
<i>When that happens,
you just have to read anything.</i>

100
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,836
<i>It will help you.</i>

101
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:42,516
<i>That's why I had them all
addressed to you and Soon Ho, but</i>

102
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:45,406
<i>Soon Ho never reads.</i>

103
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:47,866
<i>I guess she doesn't have
any challenges or heartbreaks.</i>

104
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:50,296
It's good to not have any.

105
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,476
When will you come?

106
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,826
Soon Ho worries about you a lot.

107
00:07:53,850 --> 00:07:56,566
<i>I'll go when it's time.</i>

108
00:07:56,590 --> 00:07:58,686
<i>Let her know I'll be
visiting before it gets hot.</i>

109
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:01,890
<i>If it gets hot here,
it's too much for me to handle.</i>

110
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,770
It's already nice.

111
00:08:07,110 --> 00:08:09,820
<i>4 am</i>

112
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,530
<i>4:02 am</i>

113
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,210
<i>A leaf,</i>

114
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:44,330
<i>without anyone noticing,</i>

115
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:50,356
I was just curious.

116
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:51,830
About what?

117
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:59,400
Kim Ji Soo. Moon Ha Won's fixed point.

118
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:04,546
The center coordinate which remains
no matter how things may be distorted.

119
00:09:04,570 --> 00:09:05,914
The sense of urgency which is pushing

120
00:09:05,938 --> 00:09:07,576
Ha Won's technical
skill to its outermost limit.

121
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:10,950
Perhaps it is this person. If it is,

122
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,856
all research must have
started from Kim Ji Soo.

123
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,596
Testing of Kim Ji Soo device has finished.

124
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:18,526
The hint regarding the next step is here.

125
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:22,310
Get rid of it. Discard everything
now when I'm watching you.

126
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:29,890
Right now. Immediately.

127
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:37,356
<i>Program deletion in progress...</i>

128
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,546
<i>Deleting the program...</i>

129
00:09:39,570 --> 00:09:41,500
I erased everything.

130
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:45,976
- I don't understand.
- Of course.

131
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:50,546
How frustrating it is to not be able to
understand with that good brain of yours.

132
00:09:50,570 --> 00:09:53,946
So separate yourself.
Go over there.

133
00:09:53,970 --> 00:09:54,825
R2 team.

134
00:09:54,849 --> 00:09:57,486
That's right,
R2 team. You know it well. Join them.

135
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:59,256
They will be happy to see you there.

136
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,320
I don't want to.

137
00:10:00,345 --> 00:10:03,416
If it's somewhere Moon Ha Won and
Kim Hoon are not, I'm not going anywhere.

138
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:06,796
Kim Ji Soo? Who is she? Who?
I don't have any interest at all.

139
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:09,370
Don't have any interest.

140
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:21,476
Hey that Jin Hwan. The
kid is such a clever bastard.

141
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:24,256
The fixed point never changes, but!

142
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,606
It should satisfy the conditions
to be the Lefschetz numbers...

143
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:32,170
and it only exist in the condition
interval and Anti-Ha Won interval...

144
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:37,570
Sit up.

145
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,580
Lean here.

146
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:47,166
The veins in your eyeballs
are about to explode.

147
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:50,930
You can't sleep again?
You need sleep though.

148
00:10:55,230 --> 00:10:58,860
Student Jin Soo!
Are you going to have breakfast?

149
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,836
Student Jin Soo!

150
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:05,900
He must be really tired.

151
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:09,246
You're sleeping with the
gown on! It's creating wrinkles!

152
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:11,256
Take it off and sleep!

153
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,386
What? What's going on?

154
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:17,296
I'll take it off him!

155
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:20,406
Let's do it together.

156
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:22,166
Oh no, Jin Soo!

157
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:24,966
What's wrong with you?

158
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:29,070
Look at this. I have to wash it again.

159
00:11:33,330 --> 00:11:37,306
Director, where is Teacher Kang?

160
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:40,986
I've known In Wook for a long time.

161
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:44,636
This is the first recording we've
done with a major record label.

162
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:48,480
Of all times,
he has a slump and feels betrayed.

163
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,936
In Wook is not in the right
sense of mind right now.

164
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,950
He can just do it by himself, then.

165
00:11:55,230 --> 00:11:57,036
That is....

166
00:11:57,060 --> 00:12:00,206
I've never heard that answer before.

167
00:12:00,230 --> 00:12:03,016
We record when we're
performing at our best,

168
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:05,286
not when we're at our lowest.

169
00:12:05,310 --> 00:12:08,866
Then after setting a goal, he can
just work to bring his skill up to that.

170
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:10,536
It's easy for you to say.

171
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:13,746
Let's do it! Let's do that!
Will you do that for me?

172
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:16,166
If the roots aren't rotten,
then it will live.

173
00:12:16,190 --> 00:12:18,280
Where is Teacher Kang?

174
00:12:19,450 --> 00:12:21,150
In the studio.

175
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:24,980
Really.

176
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:59,096
- Hello Teacher Kang.
- Turn the lights off.

177
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:02,116
You don't have anything to tell me?

178
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:03,700
About what?

179
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,496
About yesterday.

180
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,079
Are you not the one who
made all the commotion

181
00:13:08,103 --> 00:13:09,416
about opening up
the recording studio?

182
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,346
I ran like a crazy person!

183
00:13:11,370 --> 00:13:13,156
How long did you want me to wait?

184
00:13:13,180 --> 00:13:16,236
- You couldn't wait the 10 minutes?
- I waited for 20 minutes.

185
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:17,816
This or that. They're the same.

186
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,830
If you weren't going to
wait then at least text me!

187
00:13:20,854 --> 00:13:22,696
Turn off the lights and leave.

188
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,766
I'm just getting started.

189
00:13:24,790 --> 00:13:30,286
In your slump, do you know the
Studio Moon recording room or not?

190
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:33,836
Record by yourself,
and release an album. What's the problem?

191
00:13:33,860 --> 00:13:37,086
With Han Seo Woo, our recording
studio will help you as much as possible.

192
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:39,606
All you have to do is have the right mind.

193
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:42,060
You have my business card, right?

194
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:46,590
- I gave you my card.
- I have it!

195
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,866
Now you seem like a person
after yelling out like that.

196
00:13:51,890 --> 00:13:53,880
Give me a call!

197
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:09,627
I found Kang In Wook and
talked business with him.

198
00:14:09,652 --> 00:14:11,126
Did you see the schedule?

199
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,730
No.

200
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:16,986
Did you sleep at your house in Seoul?

201
00:14:17,010 --> 00:14:18,796
I have a house in Seoul?

202
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:21,006
The house where you
slept in after drinking.

203
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:23,546
That house! No.

204
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:26,276
Wait. No. I can just live there.

205
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,136
But there's someone living there already.

206
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,296
<i>I can just make it mine.</i>

207
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:34,486
What about the person
actually living there?

208
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:37,096
<i>It's family matters.
I asked if you saw the schedule.</i>

209
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:39,316
I'm on my way to take
a look at the schedule.

210
00:14:39,340 --> 00:14:42,140
<i>Don't go. It's a audio recording.</i>

211
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:46,066
- That...
- Yes.

212
00:14:46,090 --> 00:14:48,906
Like Kim Ji Soo. You don't want to do it,
right?

213
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:52,216
Let's just check on the time
and give it to someone else.

214
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:54,565
<i>Since we only need to
lend them the recording studio.</i>

215
00:14:54,590 --> 00:14:55,590
I'll do it.

216
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:04,520
<i>STUDIO MOON, Seoul Jongrogu Sejongro 12-9</i>

217
00:15:13,170 --> 00:15:14,870
Hello-

218
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:19,706
Can I take a picture? To put on Instagram?

219
00:15:19,730 --> 00:15:21,496
<i>Someone introduced me to this place.</i>

220
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:24,040
<i>If I do end up staying here,
save the room at the end for me.</i>

221
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:29,200
Uh,
your face is showing. It's still showing.

222
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:42,076
We'll start with simple consonants
and vowels, and then some phrases.

223
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,666
I just have to read this?

224
00:15:43,690 --> 00:15:48,026
