00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,416
- Shall we take a break?
- I want to put it on Instagram.

247
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,240
I have to post at 1 pm.

248
00:17:32,910 --> 00:17:34,480
It's good now.

249
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:37,086
We'll resume with the recording then.

250
00:17:37,110 --> 00:17:38,960
Where was the page again..

251
00:17:40,030 --> 00:17:43,010
I can't see the words very well.

252
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:49,176
- Where is the garbage?
- Give it to me.

253
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,666
Sorry.

254
00:17:50,690 --> 00:17:54,790
I can't do this twice. I'm so tired.

255
00:17:57,850 --> 00:17:59,916
You've emptied the room at the end, right?

256
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:01,840
Empty it.

257
00:18:03,910 --> 00:18:05,430
Yes.

258
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:11,920
She remembers.

259
00:18:14,310 --> 00:18:17,516
There was one from Heikin...

260
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:19,630
Where did it go?

261
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,410
Take it.

262
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:41,910
<i>Mr. Dawn, the file name for the
voice recording is Kim Min Jung.</i>

263
00:19:10,670 --> 00:19:13,890
<i>Where are you Mr. Dawn?</i>

264
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:47,610
Me, I'm Mr. Dawn.

265
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:56,686
So you've missed Mr. Dawn a lot.

266
00:19:56,710 --> 00:19:57,368
That's...

267
00:19:57,393 --> 00:19:59,316
I'm talking to that
person from that time.

268
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:03,800
Exactly. That person. Is me.

269
00:20:06,060 --> 00:20:08,976
You must be craving coffee since
you just woke up. What would you like?

270
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:12,070
I didn't sleep! I was just thinking.

271
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:15,570
Okay.

272
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:33,600
You're okay with having a cup
of coffee with Mr. Dawn, right?

273
00:20:39,470 --> 00:20:41,920
Why are you glaring at Mr. Dawn?

274
00:20:43,340 --> 00:20:44,646
- You cried, didn't you?
- No.

275
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:45,690
Your face right now
looks like you were crying.

276
00:20:45,714 --> 00:20:46,027
I don't cry.

277
00:20:46,051 --> 00:20:48,146
How can a person not cry?

278
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:49,980
I don't cry.

279
00:20:51,330 --> 00:20:54,506
Oh, I've cried once when my mom
put mustard into my cold noodles.

280
00:20:54,530 --> 00:20:58,260
I don't have any other memory of crying.

281
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:00,820
It's hot.

282
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:13,456
I did come earlier than the assigned rent
time, but I'll leave after I drink this.

283
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:16,640
I'll leave. I'm done.

284
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,080
It's hot!

285
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,980
Are you going to quit?

286
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:53,250
Don't have to quit though...

287
00:21:57,010 --> 00:22:01,840
Yes, I'm going to show
you the sample of quitting.

288
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:05,886
I started it for my own happiness,

289
00:22:05,910 --> 00:22:09,900
but now it doesn't matter.
I'm going to quit it for sure.

290
00:22:11,410 --> 00:22:14,936
Because Ha Won, that guy,
isn't an ordinary man.

291
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:18,740
I told you that he's meticulous,

292
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:24,770
wait, no, not meticulous, I think.

293
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:31,060
It's for your own happiness, Seo Woo,
then why should you quit it?

294
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:34,176
Ha Won is just Ha Won,

295
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:38,130
so in case of your 1%,
please just leave it alone, free.

296
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:43,670
Don't pluck it yourself.

297
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:52,146
Ha Won will do as you told him to do,

298
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:54,520
so you don't have to show him the sample.

299
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:01,966
Then, I'll leave...

300
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:04,306
It's Mr. Dawn's time,

301
00:23:04,330 --> 00:23:07,286
so Mr. Dawn must clean
the room before he leaves.

302
00:23:07,310 --> 00:23:11,023
And don't touch my stuffs
without permission, and...

303
00:23:11,048 --> 00:23:12,284
where is my bag?

304
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,540
Should I leave the door open?

305
00:23:16,420 --> 00:23:17,970
Close it, please.

306
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:13,980
It was dark,
so I thought you would be scared...

307
00:24:54,170 --> 00:24:55,936
Where is Chang Seop?

308
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:58,686
He will stay overnight at his parents'
house to take care of something.

309
00:24:58,710 --> 00:25:00,690
What's up with him?

310
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:02,836
Come home late tomorrow.

311
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:04,310
Why?

312
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:08,850
Chang Seop... will take a day off tomorrow.

313
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,676
You're bad at taking a hint, you know...

314
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:13,926
Ah, I see, okay.

315
00:25:13,950 --> 00:25:16,880
The snug time for two of you only?

316
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:21,906
As we have a vacant room,
why don't you move up?

317
00:25:21,931 --> 00:25:23,736
I'll give you a discount.

318
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:26,100
Not yet.

319
00:25:28,050 --> 00:25:31,876
Unnie, if I say 1%,

320
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:35,870
would it be a possibility or a false hope?

321
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:42,346
If you think of it as "as much as 1%",
it is a possibility,

322
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:45,320
and if you think of it as "a mere 1%",
then it's a false hope.

323
00:25:46,630 --> 00:25:48,290
What is it about?

324
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,620
One-sided love.

325
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:54,706
You're doing it by yourself already,
so why don't you keep it to yourself?

326
00:25:54,730 --> 00:25:56,760
I'm going to throw it out there.

327
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:02,546
I'll throw this 1% over there,

328
00:26:02,570 --> 00:26:05,216
and I'll keep watching how it survives,

329
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,466
if it really survives,

330
00:26:07,490 --> 00:26:11,716
or if it just crawls and falls down.

331
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:13,186
I'll raise it strongly.

332
00:26:13,210 --> 00:26:16,340
Are you saying to keep doing it or not?

333
00:26:35,140 --> 00:26:37,170
<i>Mr. Kang</i>

334
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,666
Sweetheart! Sweetheart!

335
00:26:39,690 --> 00:26:42,876
Mr. Kang said he would
work with you for his record.

336
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:46,430
I suggested it. Wow, it's awesome!

337
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,136
<i>Mr. Kang, this is Han Seo Woo.</i>

338
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:03,176
<i>I heard from Ms. Moon,</i>

339
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:06,750
<i>I will do my best.
See you later in the afternoon.</i>

340
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:20,030
<i>Why did Ji Soo have
Han Seo Woo's number...?</i>

341
00:27:21,450 --> 00:27:23,980
Why Han Seo Woo?

342
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,660
<i>Employee - Choi Soo
Ji / NH Nonghyup Bank</i>

343
00:27:56,130 --> 00:27:57,660
What's up?

344
00:27:59,290 --> 00:28:01,692
It was a good time
to get served with

345
00:28:01,716 --> 00:28:04,716
breakfast by Eun Joo every morning,
wasn't it?

346
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:06,586
Have you been doing well?

347
00:28:06,610 --> 00:28:08,786
You're not concerned about me,
so why bother?

348
00:28:08,810 --> 00:28:10,860
I just asked.

349
00:28:12,510 --> 00:28:14,126
Why are you having breakfast here?

350
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:15,436
Worked overnight.

351
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:18,176
Are you doing well with Eun Joo Unnie?

352
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:20,306
You're not even curious about it,
so don't bother.

353
00:28:20,330 --> 00:28:22,820
Never mind, then.

354
00:28:24,790 --> 00:28:26,496
What's wrong?

355
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:29,696
Seeing you having a
hard time because of me,

356
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:32,576
- I feel bad. - What?
- Frankly speaking,

357
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:36,126
you liked me, didn't you?
Isn't that why you were so upset and left?

358
00:28:36,150 --> 00:28:38,226
- Are you crazy?
- These days,

359
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:41,366
there are a lot of girls
who like me at my office too.

360
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:45,206
The older I get,
the cooler I become. I'm that type.

361
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:48,540
My broad chest makes my suit look so great.

362
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,046
As my status gets better suddenly,

363
00:28:53,070 --> 00:28:55,376
now I reflect on me whether
I made a wrong choice too.

364
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:58,866
You son of... I told you I'm
going to kill you if you break up!

365
00:28:58,890 --> 00:29:03,040
Undies, socks, shirts...

366
00:29:21,660 --> 00:29:23,576
<i>This is the person who made
a contract for the end room.</i>

367
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:25,346
<i>I'm going to move in today.</i>

368
00:29:25,370 --> 00:29:29,730
C-contract? I haven't made it though.

369
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:33,606
HEY! You guys even received
my deposit fee. That boy!

370
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:36,806
Chang Seop or whatever!
How dare you try to con me...

371
00:29:36,830 --> 00:29:38,286
<i>(in informal/rude speech)</i> Hey,
didn't you receive my deposit?

372
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:42,090
W-W-What did you say?

373
00:29:44,170 --> 00:29:47,635
I did. I've wired that deposit
to your account right away.

374
00:29:47,660 --> 00:29:48,786
Check the balance.

375
00:29:48,810 --> 00:29:51,326
<i>I've selected a person
who wouldn't have breakfast.</i>

376
00:29:51,350 --> 00:29:53,326
Why did you make such a contract?

377
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:55,556
Why are you making a
fuss when I helped you?

378
00:29:55,580 --> 00:29:57,926
We should see the person's personality
and character before making a decision!

379
00:29:57,950 --> 00:30:01,149
Since when did you check the
character before letting a tenant in?

380
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:02,536
I've worked so hard for this!

381
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:04,510
Damn.

382
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,720
Damn it!

383
00:30:21,020 --> 00:30:23,046
Hello.

384
00:30:23,070 --> 00:30:26,520
Earlier... The phone call...

385
00:30:27,390 --> 00:30:28,870
- <i>(in formal speech) </i>Let's go.
- Yes.

386
00:30:38,390 --> 00:30:40,446
<i>(in informal speech)</i> I clearly
said I wanted the room at the end.

387
00:30:40,470 --> 00:30:42,936
When.. did you...?

388
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:47,050
<i>(in formal speach)</i> I've mentioned several
times that I want the room at the end.

389
00:30:48,170 --> 00:30:49,340
Uh, well...

390
00:30:49,365 --> 00:30:52,826
When did you...,
how many times?

391
00:30:52,850 --> 00:30:55,830
I SAID TO THAT GIRL IN
THE RECORDING STUDIO!

392
00:30:58,970 --> 00:31:00,796
Well, since it turns out this way,

393
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:03,012
please leave,
we already have a tenant in that room.

394
00:31:03,037 --> 00:31:04,436
I'll send the
deposit back to you.

395
00:31:04,460 --> 00:31:06,086
<i>(in informal/rude speach)</i> I won't leave.

396
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:09,440
Until you give me that room,
I won't move a step from here.

397
00:31:10,170 --> 00:31:14,300
I clearly told that girl in the recording
studio about the room at the end.

398
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:20,360
A girl in the recording studio...
Must be Han Seo Woo...

399
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,120
Let me check first.

400
00:31:30,830 --> 00:31:33,586
DAMN IT,
WHY THE FUCK IS SHE NOT PICKING UP!

401
00:31:33,610 --> 00:31:37,446
Pick up, pick up the phone,
Han Seo Woo! Han Seo Woo, you...

402
00:31:37,470 --> 00:31:39,506
YOU'D BETTER PICK IT UP!

403
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:44,086
Pick up, pick up, pick up, pick up,
pick up, PICK UP! PICK UP!!!!

404
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:48,256
Pick up, pick up, pick up,
PICK UP, PICK U~~~~P!!

405
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,870
PICK UP THE PHONE!!

406
00:32:22,740 --> 00:32:24,620
You're here, sir.

407
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:29,286
Let's have a talk first today.

408
00:32:29,310 --> 00:32:31,706
We can record 3 to 4 songs for a test too.

409
00:32:31,730 --> 00:32:35,030
I should do a good job,
as this is my first time.

410
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:40,576
Mr. Kang, who is he...?

411
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:43,070
The engineer who will work with me.

412
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:52,500
But I heard from Ms. Moon
that you would work with me.

413
00:32:54,630 --> 00:32:56,036
If you could please explain...

414
00:32:56,060 --> 00:32:59,060
I don't recall saying I would
work with you, Seo Woo.

415
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:01,870
Shut the door and leave.

416
00:33:15,020 --> 00:33:17,366
- Where are you going?
- I'm checking out early.

417
00:33:17,390 --> 00:33:19,256
What do you mean, go?
Where are you going?

418
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:22,490
- He came with another sound engineer.
- What?

419
00:33:24,730 --> 00:33:27,110
What the heck is she saying?

420
00:33:42,430 --> 00:33:44,170
Come up.

421
00:33:45,270 --> 00:33:47,416
He definitely said that
he'd be working with you.

422
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:50,990
- He must've changed his mind, then.
- In the span of a few hours?

423
00:33:51,890 --> 00:33:54,656
I've known Teacher Kang from before.

424
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,696
He's not that kind of person.
Plus he's in a slump.

425
00:33:56,720 --> 00:34:00,020
If he's in a slump,
then can he treat other people rudely?

426
00:34:00,045 --> 00:34:01,426
Don't yield to such whim.

427
00:34:01,450 --> 00:34:02,606
Follow me.

428
00:34:02,630 --> 00:34:06,456
I'm fine. Really, Manager.

429
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,676
Are you okay?

430
00:34:07,700 --> 00:34:09,566
Are you stupid?

431
00:34:09,590 --> 00:34:13,656
If I think of such things as yield,
then I can't do anything.

432
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:18,276
In the process of work, there can be
some misunderstandings and mistakes.

433
00:34:18,300 --> 00:34:20,360
I'm fine.

434
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:40,350
It's unfair, but why am I not even mad?

435
00:34:48,890 --> 00:34:50,866
Let's hold it in, hold it in.

436
00:34:50,890 --> 00:34:55,590
Soon Ho, you should hold it in,
so that you can live in Seoul.

437
00:34:58,340 --> 00:35:00,526
She ran away?

438
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:04,176
Han Seo Woo ran away,
but... oh, I'm so mad.

439
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:06,786
It's always the good-mannered
ones who run away first.

440
00:35:06,810 --> 00:35:08,226
Where did she run off to?

441
00:35:08,250 --> 00:35:11,976
I don't know. She was walking away quietly,
but-

442
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:16,186
I'm so pissed off! It broke my heart!

443
00:35:16,210 --> 00:35:19,276
Han Seo Woo has really
gotten on In Wook's side, too.

444
00:35:19,300 --> 00:35:21,699
She explained to me that
there are a lot of unknown

445
00:35:21,723 --> 00:35:23,866
but great talented musicians in Korea,
and...

446
00:35:23,890 --> 00:35:27,680
Kang In Wook, that jerk...
I hate backstabbing the most.

447
00:35:28,620 --> 00:35:31,296
Then it's the fault of
Kang what's-his-name.

448
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:35,746
What's pissing me off more
is that I'm bearing with it.

449
00:35:35,770 --> 00:35:37,900
Why are you bearing with it?

450
00:35:39,070 --> 00:35:41,376
That's what I'm saying!

451
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:44,180
He's so freaking immature.

452
00:35:53,470 --> 00:35:57,296
Kang In Wook, you definitely said

453
00:35:57,320 --> 00:36:00,136
that you'd be working with Han Seo Woo,
that you'd try it out.

454
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:02,856
I heard it, as clear as day.

455
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:07,490
Han Seo Woo must have felt pretty bad.

456
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:11,226
There was a situation that called for it.

457
00:36:11,250 --> 00:36:14,656
Mr. Kang, insulting others to
this extent is like a habit for you.

458
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:16,776
- I'll explain.
- Do it by yourself.

459
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,506
Since you're paying us rent for it anyway.

460
00:36:18,530 --> 00:36:21,366
Using all the time,
you can try your best to explain,

461
00:36:21,390 --> 00:36:23,610
or just pound away at the piano.

462
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:45,060
I need some powerful healing.

