00:39:20,690 --> 00:39:27,890
♫ <i>Reaching my hand out to the night sky,
I make a wish</i> ♫

486
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:32,080
♫ <i>I'm really missing you</i> ♫

487
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:56,866
<i>February 27th (scratched out)</i>

488
00:39:56,890 --> 00:39:58,806
<i>Are you going to Oslo?</i>

489
00:39:58,830 --> 00:40:00,850
<i>Should I go?</i>

490
00:40:03,660 --> 00:40:06,526
<i>You should've hidden it with all you had.</i>

491
00:40:06,550 --> 00:40:09,306
If you don't know,
then it doesn't mean anything.

492
00:40:09,330 --> 00:40:12,096
As tiring and painful as it was,
you should've hidden it.

493
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:15,560
- You should've hidden it with all you...
- Why can't you understand me? Why?

494
00:40:16,670 --> 00:40:19,300
You know I didn't even do it on purpose.

495
00:40:21,170 --> 00:40:24,106
I'm telling you it was a mistake.

496
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:30,250
Just tell me once that it's okay.
If you do that, I can somehow live, Ji Soo.

497
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,600
Is this a good time?

498
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:51,060
Just a moment is enough.

499
00:41:06,770 --> 00:41:09,420
Alcohol? Dinner?

500
00:41:37,070 --> 00:41:39,906
The manager and Teacher
Kang are there together.

501
00:41:39,930 --> 00:41:42,836
Soon Ho is there?

502
00:41:42,860 --> 00:41:44,406
Why are the two of them together?

503
00:41:44,430 --> 00:41:49,936
They're fighting, most likely.
Soon Ho called me because she was mad.

504
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:52,886
Soon Ho hates when promises are broken.

505
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:55,706
She did seem to be acting a bit sensitive.

506
00:41:55,730 --> 00:41:58,440
It's more than being sensitive.

507
00:41:59,470 --> 00:42:03,262
Because of that,
she turned her back to the world and

508
00:42:03,287 --> 00:42:06,044
for about 9 years,
she lived in a farm.

509
00:42:13,670 --> 00:42:15,390
No, but...

510
00:42:16,670 --> 00:42:18,936
So you were rejected as soon as you came?

511
00:42:18,960 --> 00:42:22,590
After so many years, she said to
meet up and you met up, then rejection?

512
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:27,496
Wow, I'm starting to cry.

513
00:42:27,520 --> 00:42:30,190
Wow, what's up with Kim Ji Soo?

514
00:42:31,090 --> 00:42:34,616
Backstabbing is dramatic in every form.

515
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:38,830
The first time I see you,
Uncle, and I really like it.

516
00:42:41,620 --> 00:42:46,190
Wow, how is this possible?
Birds of a feather flock together.

517
00:43:08,490 --> 00:43:10,927
<i>She was even engaged to her first love,</i>

518
00:43:10,952 --> 00:43:14,766
<i>but he fell in love with her best friend,
so they called it off.</i>

519
00:43:14,790 --> 00:43:20,826
She took me to a snack bar to console me,
but ended up wailing herself.

520
00:43:20,850 --> 00:43:23,926
After that, she gave up on
Seoul and went down to the farm.

521
00:43:23,950 --> 00:43:26,596
And she became a gardener.

522
00:43:26,621 --> 00:43:31,404
Soon Ho is a child
with a very fragile heart.

523
00:43:34,530 --> 00:43:38,390
There aren't a lot of places we can go...
Are you really hungry?

524
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:45,700
I was worried about you.

525
00:43:55,610 --> 00:43:59,506
Well, now, can you tell me your story?

526
00:43:59,530 --> 00:44:01,146
Wait, if you don't have anything to say,
let me start first.

527
00:44:01,170 --> 00:44:03,576
Please come to the studio as per
the reservation by the end of this week.

528
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:07,806
As Han Seo Woo said, this can happen
due to some misunderstanding or mistake.

529
00:44:07,830 --> 00:44:09,366
And for the new reservation,

530
00:44:09,391 --> 00:44:13,316
I don't care if you do it in another
place with a fresh mind or whatever.

531
00:44:13,340 --> 00:44:16,496
You care for Seo Woo a lot.
Are you two close?

532
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:18,091
I'm not close with anyone.

533
00:44:18,116 --> 00:44:20,846
I'm not an affectional
person to begin with.

534
00:44:20,870 --> 00:44:23,160
Life is originally starting
and ending by oneself, so

535
00:44:23,184 --> 00:44:25,456
I'm planning to live
lonesomely as much as possible.

536
00:44:25,480 --> 00:44:26,906
But why to Han Seo Woo...?

537
00:44:26,930 --> 00:44:30,436
Mr. Kang In Wook,
when a person cares for another,

538
00:44:30,460 --> 00:44:32,425
you're not supposed to
approach it in a way "because

539
00:44:32,449 --> 00:44:34,176
one likes the other,
or is close to another".

540
00:44:34,200 --> 00:44:36,646
This is simply about a promise.

541
00:44:36,670 --> 00:44:40,276
You broke your promise,
and Han Seo Woo was sad about it.

542
00:44:40,300 --> 00:44:42,790
And it makes me feel shitty.

543
00:44:46,090 --> 00:44:51,346
Seo Woo... did you first
meet her in the studio?

544
00:44:51,370 --> 00:44:53,936
That was the first time I got to know her.

545
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:58,356
As soon as we started working together,
she helped me with a difficult task.

546
00:44:58,380 --> 00:45:01,346
To buy dishes through on-line shopping,
I didn't want to use my own name.

547
00:45:01,370 --> 00:45:03,276
She bought them for me.

548
00:45:03,300 --> 00:45:07,566
Well, although it can be nothing,
someone might take it suspiciously.

549
00:45:07,590 --> 00:45:09,336
"Why doesn't she buy them herself?"

550
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:13,680
"Does she have a credit delinquency?"
I would be doubtful too.

551
00:45:17,280 --> 00:45:21,036
Same for your slump too. In different
angles, many would be doubtful...

552
00:45:21,060 --> 00:45:23,990
D-Dishes... Who did you buy them from?

553
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:31,166
It's selling and buying though
online shops. How would I know that?

554
00:45:31,190 --> 00:45:35,396
Right, even when selling them,
all you need are address and phone number.

555
00:45:35,420 --> 00:45:37,056
You don't have to see the faces either...

556
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:39,410
Obviously.

557
00:45:43,660 --> 00:45:46,826
I'll work with Han Seo
Woo for my next album.

558
00:45:46,850 --> 00:45:48,900
Are you kidding me?

559
00:45:51,120 --> 00:45:53,390
No, not at all.

560
00:45:58,850 --> 00:46:00,036
Are you enjoying those dishes?

561
00:46:00,060 --> 00:46:02,096
Those are not for me either.

562
00:46:02,120 --> 00:46:05,040
I got that request from another person too.

563
00:46:11,070 --> 00:46:15,350
Life is disgustingly twisted, you know.

564
00:46:17,960 --> 00:46:20,710
By the way, why do you keep laughing?

565
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:26,010
No, just... I'm just dumbfounded,
that's all.

566
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:32,540
We ran out of sandwiches, I'm sorry.

567
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:38,746
Then what about ramen?

568
00:46:38,770 --> 00:46:40,626
Eat here?

569
00:46:40,650 --> 00:46:44,150
Ramen you eat at a cafe is so delicious,
you know.

570
00:46:47,940 --> 00:46:50,190
<i>Close - see you next time</i>

571
00:47:00,140 --> 00:47:03,096
Shall I... testify that
you've waited long time?

572
00:47:03,120 --> 00:47:07,056
<i>- She must not be coming today either.
- She will, one day.</i>

573
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:10,760
<i>If I meet her, I'll testify for you
how you've been waiting so far.</i>

574
00:47:15,220 --> 00:47:17,000
No...

575
00:47:18,170 --> 00:47:22,490
The person I was waiting
for was someone else.

576
00:47:23,690 --> 00:47:26,530
- I know her too.
- I see...

577
00:47:27,530 --> 00:47:30,550
After that, have you met her?

578
00:47:34,020 --> 00:47:35,356
No.

579
00:47:35,380 --> 00:47:38,936
My cafe is where the waiting
usually ends up with the meeting.

580
00:47:38,961 --> 00:47:41,396
Each cafe has a different energy,
you know.

581
00:47:41,420 --> 00:47:45,016
When I saw a person who got stood up,
that made me feel sad too,

582
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:47,716
but the very next day,
they showed up together.

583
00:47:47,740 --> 00:47:50,020
You will meet her eventually.

584
00:47:58,040 --> 00:48:00,150
I'm sorry.

585
00:48:34,590 --> 00:48:37,160
I shouldn't have brought it up...

586
00:48:38,020 --> 00:48:43,590
No, he should've cried already.

587
00:48:49,860 --> 00:48:55,520
On that table,
you were with another lady, weren't you?

588
00:48:58,420 --> 00:49:04,996
That lady, she was looking up the
ceiling when she was waiting for you,

589
00:49:05,020 --> 00:49:07,140
so I still remember her.

590
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,740
She was the person.

591
00:49:14,280 --> 00:49:16,370
The one he waited for.

592
00:49:19,300 --> 00:49:21,500
Oh, she came though.

593
00:49:46,990 --> 00:49:53,170
<i>Seo Woo, would you please
tell Won not to wait at the cafe?</i>

594
00:50:15,640 --> 00:50:20,986
By any chance, are you the same person
who said has never cried all his life?

595
00:50:21,010 --> 00:50:25,206
I can c-cry too, I found that out today.

596
00:50:25,230 --> 00:50:29,480
Moreover, didn't you come to me
because you're worried about me?

597
00:50:31,350 --> 00:50:33,920
I didn't come to show you this...

598
00:50:34,900 --> 00:50:36,796
It totally cheers me up.

599
00:50:36,820 --> 00:50:40,896
Why do I feel refreshed when
I saw someone else crying?

600
00:50:40,920 --> 00:50:42,466
Let's go.

601
00:50:42,490 --> 00:50:44,906
To where?

602
00:50:44,930 --> 00:50:46,870
Taxi~!

603
00:50:53,130 --> 00:50:55,206
You must feel embarrassed,

604
00:50:55,230 --> 00:50:58,020
why are you waving at the empty street?

605
00:51:06,690 --> 00:51:09,890
Nice to meet you, Ha Won.

606
00:51:12,120 --> 00:51:14,590
So, can I be Ha Won now?

607
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:25,350
Do you have anything to say to Mr. Dawn?
I guess he won't show up going forward.

608
00:51:28,610 --> 00:51:32,080
So,
this is the last moment with Mr. Dawn...?

609
00:51:34,370 --> 00:51:37,380
I can't tell him not to leave though.

610
00:51:43,210 --> 00:51:45,306
Would you please turn around?

611
00:51:45,330 --> 00:51:47,806
Just say it, please.

612
00:51:47,830 --> 00:51:50,320
Since you're Mr. Dawn?

613
00:52:03,840 --> 00:52:07,780
Mr. Dawn, good bye.

614
00:52:09,500 --> 00:52:11,900
I was thankful.

615
00:52:16,060 --> 00:52:17,880
That's it.

616
00:52:24,270 --> 00:52:26,410
Taxi!

617
00:52:37,050 --> 00:52:39,576
Kim Ji Soo!

618
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:42,736
Make some noise!

619
00:52:42,760 --> 00:52:47,070
Ah, Ji Soo! Turn on some fun music!

620
00:52:48,930 --> 00:52:52,200
What is it? Why isn't the music on?

621
00:52:53,260 --> 00:52:55,260
Kim Ji Soo?

622
00:52:56,740 --> 00:52:58,966
Did he change it?

623
00:52:58,990 --> 00:53:02,296
Huh,
you think I won't be able to find you guys?

624
00:53:02,320 --> 00:53:06,370
Genie? Siri?

625
00:53:17,690 --> 00:53:18,836
Device?

626
00:53:18,860 --> 00:53:21,800
No, please listen.

627
00:53:35,900 --> 00:53:41,560
This piece... when I first saw you.

628
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:00,726
<i>I remember,</i>

629
00:54:00,750 --> 00:54:03,731
<i>when I looked outside,
some man was looking around,</i>

630
00:54:03,756 --> 00:54:06,126
<i>so I turned it up so
that he could listen.</i>

631
00:54:06,150 --> 00:54:09,600
Oh my, oh my, so it was you, Ha Won?

632
00:54:10,590 --> 00:54:13,646
So you remember the
moment when you first saw me.

633
00:54:13,670 --> 00:54:15,266
It's vivid,

634
00:54:15,290 --> 00:54:17,646
I heard this song,
so I looked up.

635
00:54:17,671 --> 00:54:20,516
And went to the studio
and you were there.

636
00:54:20,540 --> 00:54:25,576
I told you, that the relationship lasts
long if the first impression was vivid.

637
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:29,436
I must be so impressive then, am I right?

638
00:54:29,460 --> 00:54:31,330
Of course.

639
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:38,326
But the first encounter I remember was
when you were in the recording booth.

640
00:54:38,350 --> 00:54:43,436
It's a different scene. If we remember
differently, that what happens?

641
00:54:43,460 --> 00:54:46,990
Then, keep watching what would happen next.

642
00:54:48,320 --> 00:54:51,146
Are you feeling better?

643
00:54:51,170 --> 00:54:53,880
I told you this story to
make you feel better.

644
00:54:54,780 --> 00:54:59,150
After seeing you crying earlier,
I forgot all about the upsetting work.

645
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:16,706
Your door looks open.

646
00:55:16,730 --> 00:55:18,136
Oh, stop, stop!

647
00:55:18,160 --> 00:55:20,430
I still have something to talk about.

648
00:55:22,810 --> 00:55:23,966
This can cause a big trouble, you know.

649
00:55:23,990 --> 00:55:26,130
Wait, wait!

650
00:55:44,050 --> 00:55:46,270
It's looks better than
looking at it from the outside.

651
00:55:46,295 --> 00:55:46,987
It's warm too.

652
00:55:47,011 --> 00:55:49,107
I live here because
it's not too bad.

653
00:55:49,132 --> 00:55:51,834
Eun Joo unnie doesn't
let me just live anywhere.

654
00:56:17,300 --> 00:56:20,440
- What about the device?
- I got rid of it.

655
00:56:22,380 --> 00:56:25,150
It sounds a bit harsh
to say I got rid of it...

656
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:33,910
In the past,
it was clear what Ji Soo gave me.

657
00:56:35,710 --> 00:56:39,370
I was happy when I thought
of Ji Soo during difficult times,

658
00:56:40,470 --> 00:56:46,350
Ji Soo could comfort me
when I was feeling empty.

659
00:56:48,220 --> 00:56:51,220
There was something that
Ji Soo could correct for me.

660
00:56:54,980 --> 00:57:01,180
Now, when I think of Ji Soo,
it's difficult.

661
00:57:08,080 --> 00:57:10,760
It's time for me to stop.

662
00:57:11,650 --> 00:57:14,796
It's ambiguous to say I'm stopping.

663
00:57:14,820 --> 00:57:20,690
But I've realized that no matter how
abstract it is, there is a way through it.

664
00:57:24,630 --> 00:57:27,060
Since I've made up my mind.

665
00:57:28,170 --> 00:57:33,200
I'm going to find out what and how to stop.

666
00:57:35,140 --> 00:57:36,890
Enough about me,...

667
00:57:38,330 --> 00:57:40,886
it's your turn.

668
00:57:40,910 --> 00:57:43,786
You told me.

669
00:57:43,810 --> 00:57:46,140
That you like looking.

670
00:57:49,560 --> 00:57:53,196
I honestly didn't know what that meant.

671
00:57:53,220 --> 00:57:57,366
I never put value in looking
at something for a long time.

672
00:57:57,390 --> 00:58:01,600
I've also believed that emotions
continue even if you've never met.

673
00:58:02,500 --> 00:58:04,780
But now I know,

674
00:58:05,900 --> 00:58:08,790
what it means to like looking at something.

675
00:58:15,290 --> 00:58:20,680
It was nice to see even
though it was difficult.

676
00:58:22,590 --> 00:58:24,550
See what?

677
00:58:42,920 --> 00:58:44,490
And,

678
00:58:47,490 --> 00:58:49,620
you didn't quit, right?

679
00:58:50,700 --> 00:58:52,996
You're talking without context again.

680
00:58:53,020 --> 00:58:57,250
It's not even 1% of the time and
I don't do that. At most it is 1%.

681
00:58:59,910 --> 00:59:05,850
I 'm really curious how your 1% will grow.

682
00:59:12,910 --> 00:59:15,796
Seo Woo!

683
00:59:15,820 --> 00:59:18,320
- Hey, Han Seo Woo!
- Excuse me.

684
00:59:19,660 --> 00:59:21,640
Han Seo Woo!

685
00:59:23,550 --> 00:59:26,176
The student was hanging
around the bus stop for a half hour.

686
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:28,566
Because I'm going to pick him up
and escort him, you go quickly on up.

687
00:59:28,590 --> 00:59:30,516
I know you're busy, but are you frozen?

688
00:59:30,540 --> 00:59:32,341
Eun Joo is working like the
devil by herself in the kitchen.

689
00:59:32,365 --> 00:59:32,917
Get going!

690
00:59:32,941 --> 00:59:35,010
Oh, right!

691
00:59:47,350 --> 00:59:51,024
We are having dinner together
when the new boarder arrives.

692
00:59:51,049 --> 00:59:52,286
I completely forgot.

693
00:59:52,310 --> 00:59:55,340
If I fail to show up, Eun Joo will kill me.

694
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:08,600
There's one more thing.

695
01:00:09,370 --> 01:00:14,030
When I made up my mind, I thought it
would be better for you to know everything.

696
01:00:15,940 --> 01:00:19,660
Among the things Ji Soo wanted to tell you,

697
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:23,290
there is one more.

698
01:00:30,680 --> 01:00:35,740
Ji Soo went to the place
you had agreed to meet at.

699
01:00:43,330 --> 01:00:44,465
Oh. Seo Woo.

700
01:00:44,490 --> 01:00:47,870
Put a little soy sauce
in the japchae. It's bland.

701
01:00:47,900 --> 01:00:50,000
Yes.

702
01:00:56,110 --> 01:00:58,576
This alley is a little confusing.

703
01:00:58,600 --> 01:01:02,086
There's just one butcher shop in the
alley leading to our boarding house.

704
01:01:02,110 --> 01:01:02,908
A butcher shop?

705
01:01:02,933 --> 01:01:06,527
Yes. But next to it,
the sweet sour chicken is delicious.

706
01:01:06,552 --> 01:01:07,749
Butcher shop.

707
01:02:05,990 --> 01:02:08,700
<i>If I had only turned around.</i>

708
01:02:20,110 --> 01:02:22,020
<i>Ji Soo!</i>

709
01:02:23,150 --> 01:02:25,830
<i>Quitting you...</i>

710
01:02:35,610 --> 01:02:40,510
<i>will put a stop my life-long regret.</i>

711
01:02:52,680 --> 01:02:55,116
Welcome.

712
01:02:55,140 --> 01:02:57,910
Feel free to eat as much as you want.

713
01:02:58,000 --> 01:03:01,495
I only ate one roll of
kimbap at 2. I appreciate it.

714
01:03:01,520 --> 01:03:02,636
Eat up.

715
01:03:02,660 --> 01:03:06,066
This household's japchae is amazing.

716
01:03:06,090 --> 01:03:08,636
Our Soo Ji is a japchae wizard.

717
01:03:08,660 --> 01:03:10,616
Who is Soo Ji?

718
01:03:10,640 --> 01:03:15,266
"She is a japchae ghost."
Why are you talking about her again?

719
01:03:15,290 --> 01:03:16,956
You're speaking without honorifics...

720
01:03:16,980 --> 01:03:18,426
That's not it.

721
01:03:18,450 --> 01:03:22,840
Ah. We are dating. Don't be concerned.

722
01:03:30,290 --> 01:03:32,080
This is delicious.

723
01:03:32,990 --> 01:03:36,930
Unni. I'm going to make a
phone call. I left my phone.

724
01:03:37,850 --> 01:03:40,020
Hurry back.

725
01:04:04,730 --> 01:04:07,570
<i>I am not quitting.</i>

726
01:04:08,680 --> 01:04:14,400
Having said that does not mean
there is nothing expected of you.

727
01:04:15,390 --> 01:04:19,560
Because I will take care
of myself so Mr. Ha Won,

728
01:04:21,000 --> 01:04:24,476
make sure you figure
out what it is. Do that.

